### 6. Trigger Rules — Detailed Flow Diagrams

#### Scenario A: User opens OthersReports page

```
OthersReports.created()
  └─ checkLastWeekSummary()
       └─ getLastWeekBounds(today)    → week_start = last Mon, week_end = last Sun
       └─ checkWeeklySummary(week_start)   → GET /daily-report/weekly-summary/check
            ├─ has_summary = true → STOP (nothing to do)
            └─ has_summary = false
                 └─ WeeklySummaryGenerator.triggerCheck()
                      └─ fetchMyReportsForWeek(lastWeek)
                           → GET /daily-report/get-my-daily-report (with decrypt_config)
                           → filter: status=1 (committed only)
                      └─ (if reports exist)
                      └─ generateWeeklySummaryStream(compressed_context)
                           → POST /daily-report/weekly-summary/generate
                           → SSE stream → accumulate summaryText
                      └─ saveWeeklySummary(summaryText + encrypt_config + authorize_config)
                           → POST /daily-report/weekly-summary/save
                           → core encrypts content, generates authorized_token
                           → server stores encrypted row
                      └─ extractProjects(summaryText)   [blocking]
                           → POST /daily-report/weekly-summary/extract-projects
                      └─ saveProjects(sfuser_id, week_start, project_names)
                           → POST /daily-report/weekly-summary/save-projects
```

#### Scenario B: User submits report on Friday

```
EditPage.submitReport(status=1)
  └─ dailyReportApis.editMyReportAPI(params)  ← existing flow
  └─ this.successEdit()                        ← existing flow
  └─ triggerWeeklySummaryAfterSubmit(reportDate)  ← NEW
       └─ dayOfWeek = Friday (5)
       └─ getCurrentWeekBounds(today)
       └─ checkWeeklySummary(week_start)
            ├─ has_summary = true → STOP
            └─ has_summary = false
                 └─ WeeklySummaryGenerator.generateForWeek(currentWeek)
                      [same flow as Scenario A from generateForWeek onwards]
```

#### Scenario C: User submits report on Saturday or Sunday

```
EditPage.submitReport(status=1)
  └─ successEdit()
  └─ triggerWeeklySummaryAfterSubmit(reportDate)
       └─ dayOfWeek = Saturday(6) or Sunday(0)
       └─ getCurrentWeekBounds(today)   ← current week includes last Mon-Sun
       └─ WeeklySummaryGenerator.generateForWeek(currentWeek)
            [ALWAYS generates, save endpoint does UPSERT so existing summary is overwritten]
```

**Note on Saturday/Sunday "current week"**: Saturday and Sunday are the end of the current ISO week (Mon-Sun). The `getCurrentWeekBounds` function must return the week that *contains* today — meaning for Saturday April 26, it returns `week_start: 2026-04-20, week_end: 2026-04-26`.

